definition.value: A radical that carries an electric charge.
A beta-D-glucoside in which the aglycone species is chrysophanol, the glycosidic linkage being to the hydroxy group at C-8.
An oxo steroid carrying an oxo group at position 20.
A tetramethoxyflavone that is  the 3,6,7,3'-tetramethyl ether derivative of quercetagetin.
An N-acylglycinate that is the conjugate base of N-benzyloxycarbonylglycine; major species at pH 7.3.
A trimethoxyflavone that is the 3,7,3'-trimethyl ether derivative of quercetagetin.
